benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Retrieve the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Request: TC01–TC04 cover retrieval of latest, by requestedDate, by accountId, and both together; assert 200, text/xml, and valid XML.
Empty Response: TC05 (no catalog) and TC15 (empty catalog structure) plus TC06 (no version at date) validate empty/not-found behaviors.
Query Parameters: TC02/TC04 (valid combos), TC07–TC08 (invalid formats), TC09 (unsupported params), TC16 (max lengths) exercise parameter handling.
Authorization: TC10 (401) and TC11 (403) cover auth failures.
Robustness/Resilience: TC12 (503), TC22 (504), and TC14 (retry after transient failure) check failure and recovery paths.
Performance/Scalability/Concurrency: TC17 (very large catalog), TC18 (concurrent requests), TC21 (peak load) validate non-functional aspects.
XML Quality/Compatibility: TC19 (well‑formed per schema) and TC20 (backward compatibility) ensure response correctness; Content-Type asserted as text/xml.
Security/Validation: TC13 covers injection attempts and ensures safe handling.
Pagination: Not applicable to this endpoint (full catalog retrieval), acceptable omission.
gaps: Caching Behavior: No tests for ETag/If-None-Match, Last-Modified/If-Modified-Since, Cache-Control headers, or 304 Not Modified flow.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No scenarios validating 429 Too Many Requests and Retry-After behavior under burst traffic.
Account-specific negatives: Missing case for valid UUID accountId with no tenant-specific catalog (or non-existent account) and expected status code.
requestedDate boundaries/timezones: No tests for exact effectiveDate boundaries, just-before/just-after transitions, or timezone/Z-offset handling.
Content negotiation: No tests asserting behavior with Accept headers (e.g., text/xml vs application/xml) and charset; defaulting behavior not verified.
Error contract consistency: Tests allow 404 or 400 interchangeably for not-found cases; no assertion of a canonical error code or structured error payload schema.
recommendations: Add caching tests: verify presence/values of ETag and Cache-Control; perform conditional GET with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since to assert 304 Not Modified.
Add rate limiting scenarios: generate burst traffic to elicit 429 Too Many Requests and validate Retry-After header and backoff behavior.
Add negative account tests: valid-but-unknown accountId and accountId with no catalog at requestedDate; assert agreed status (e.g., 404) and error schema.
Add requestedDate edge cases: exact effective date/time, one tick before/after version boundaries, timezone offsets (UTC vs local), and far-future/past dates.
Test Accept header handling: requests with Accept: text/xml and application/xml (and without Accept) to confirm correct Content-Type/charset and fallback.
Tighten error expectations: replace ambiguous “404 or 400” with definitive codes per API contract and validate a structured error body (code/message).
